---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const updated = "June 24, 2026";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy"
  description="How faizahmed.in handles your data: cookieless analytics, no tracking, and an optional newsletter."
  canonicalPath="/privacy"
>
  <div class="reading privacy">
    <h1 class="page-title">Privacy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated {updated}</p>

    <p>
      This site (<strong>faizahmed.in</strong>) is a personal profile and blog. It is
      built to respect your privacy: it sets <strong>no cookies</strong>, shows no ads,
      and collects no personal data about you unless you choose to subscribe to the
      newsletter (see below).
    </p>

    <h2>Analytics</h2>
    <p>
      Visit statistics are measured with <strong>Umami</strong>, a
      <strong>cookieless</strong>, privacy-first analytics tool. It records aggregate page
      views and referrers, with no cookies, no fingerprinting, no cross-site tracking, and
      no data that identifies you. Because it collects no personal data, no consent
      banner is required.
    </p>

    <h2>Newsletter</h2>
    <p>
      If you subscribe using the form on the site, it stores the <strong>email
      address</strong> you enter (and your name, if you choose to provide it). This is
      used for one purpose: to email you when a new post is published. It is never sold,
      rented, or shared for advertising.
    </p>
    <p>
      Subscriber emails are processed by <strong>Resend</strong>, a third-party email
      provider acting as a data processor under a signed Data Processing Agreement;
      Resend maintains SOC 2 Type II compliance. You can <strong>unsubscribe at any
      time</strong> using the link in any email, which removes you from the list.
    </p>

    <h2>Embedded content</h2>
    <p>
      Some posts embed third-party content that only loads when you choose to use it:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>YouTube videos</strong> load only after you click the thumbnail. Until
        then, nothing is requested from YouTube. Once you play a video, Google/YouTube
        may set cookies under their own privacy policy.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Diagrams</strong> on a few posts load the Mermaid library from a public
        CDN (jsDelivr) to render charts in your browser.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Hosting</h2>
    <p>
      The site is hosted on <strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong> and served through
      Cloudflare. Like any web host, Cloudflare processes basic request data (such as
      your IP address) to deliver and secure the site. See Cloudflare's privacy policy
      for details.
    </p>

    <h2>What the site does not do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>No accounts, logins, or comment forms.</li>
      <li>No advertising or third-party tracking scripts.</li>
      <li>External links open in a new tab and are governed by their own privacy policies.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your data</h2>
    <p>
      The only personal data the site stores is the email address (and optional name) of
      newsletter subscribers. You can unsubscribe at any time using the link in any email,
      which removes you from the list. To request deletion of your subscriber data, or for
      any other privacy question, reach me via the links on the
      <a href="/about">About</a> page.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .privacy { margin: 0 auto; }
  .page-title { margin: 2.2rem 0 0.2rem; }
  .updated { color: var(--text-faint); font-size: 0.85rem; margin: 0 0 1.6rem; }
  .privacy h2 { font-size: 1.15rem; margin: 1.8rem 0 0.5rem; }
  .privacy ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; }
  .privacy li { margin: 0.4rem 0; }
</style>
